$ MS Access: SQL Server Compatible Syntax (ANSI-92)

In Access, → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql[SQL Server] compatible Syntax (ANSI 92) can be enabled or disabled under
the menu → Microsoft/Office/Access/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Object-Designers/Query-Design[File -> Object Designers -> Query Design]

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/sql[SQL Server] compatible Syntax (ANSI 92)
   • This database
   • Default for new databases

The SQL compatibility mode (which by default is → misc/ISO/9075#sql-89[SQL 89, level 1] can be upgraded to SQL-92 under File -> Options -> Object Designers -> SQL Server Compatible Syntax (ANSI 92):
gh|about-Access|/options/ANSI-92-compatibility.png||

{ Changing the option with Visual Basic for Application

  With → development/languages/VBA, it is possible to set this options like so:
code {
setOption "ANSI Query Mode", 1
code }

 `setOption` is defined in the → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/Application[`Application`] object. Because this object is the default object, it does not need to be specified.

}
